# Environment Configuration Examples

# For local development with Rails server running on same machine:
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# For local development with Rails server on different machine/Docker:
API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3000

# For testing with hosted Rails server:
API_BASE_URL=https://your-rails-server.herokuapp.com

# For production deployment:
API_BASE_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com

# Notes:
# 1. Update constants/Config.ts with your chosen BASE_URL
# 2. Ensure your Rails server has CORS configured for your app's domain
# 3. For iOS Simulator, use localhost or 127.0.0.1
# 4. For physical device testing, use your computer's IP address
# 5. For production, use your production server URL